 <mixed-citation publication-type="other" id="d37e3130" class="mixed-citation">Additionally, SSP-specific population projections for children 
  <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
   <math id="M77" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
     <mn class="mn">5</mn>
     <mspace width="0.3em" class="mspace"/>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">y</mi>
     <mtext class="mtext">â€‰</mtext>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </inline-formula> of age were taken from the Wittgenstein Centre for Demography and Global Human Capital (
  <xref rid="c52" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">2017</xref>). The poverty model provided population data for children 
  <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
   <math id="M78" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
     <mn class="mn">15</mn>
     <mspace width="0.3em" class="mspace"/>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">y</mi>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </inline-formula> in agricultural and nonagricultural families; we assumed that the agricultural-to-nonagricultural ratio in children 
  <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
   <math id="M79" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
     <mn class="mn">5</mn>
     <mspace width="0.3em" class="mspace"/>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">y</mi>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </inline-formula> of age was the same as that for children 
  <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
   <math id="M80" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
     <mn class="mn">15</mn>
     <mspace width="0.3em" class="mspace"/>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">y</mi>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </inline-formula> of age. Further we assumed that agricultural populations lived in rural areas, and nonagricultural families lived in urban areas.
